# [[excessive]], {{gloss|an excess of}}
#: {{ux|fr|Il y '''en''' a '''trop'''.|t=There is '''too much of it''' — ''or'' — There are '''too many of them'''.}}
## {{q|with singulars and uncountable nouns}} [[too]] [[much]]
##: {{ux|fr|On est passé beaucoup '''trop de''' temps en compagnie de menteurs.
|'''Too much''' time is spent in the company of liars. }}
## {{q|with countable nouns}} too [[many]]
##: {{ux|fr|Il a lis '''trop d'''{{'}}histoires effrayantes et ne sait plus s'endormir.
|He read '''too many''' scary stories and can't sleep any more.}}

====Usage notes====
* As seen above, the preposition {{m|fr|de}} and the complement it introduces can be replaced with the adverbial pronoun {{m|fr|en}} to reference a previously mentioned substantive.
